The paper deals with learning and classification problems in large-scale data analysis, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of diffusion-based or spectral-based methods also suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses heavy-tailed properties of the data, which is a topic in statistics and probability theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides sample complexity bounds, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
